Package <Unnamed>

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    EOCSVInterface
    The interface is used in conjunction with EOCSV, classes that implements EOCSVInterface are can be converted to CSV lines.
    EOGUIMultiSelectInterface
    Classes that are passed to EOGUIMultiSelect must implement this class to be painted
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ContactInfo
    This is the base class for all ContactInfo classes.
    CustomerContactInfo
    This class contains information, for a specific customer.
    EOArrangement
    An implementation of an arrangement.
    EOBreadcrumb
    A que system.
    EOCSV
    This class supports 3 different export modes 1) All data from the database is exported 2) All data that specific facilitator are part off (by being part of an arrangement or an event).
    EODatabaseInterface
    The EODatabaseInterface handles all connections to the database.
    EOEvent
    EOEvents is one or more events that are linked to EOArrangement, an EOEvent cannot exist if its not linked to and EOArrangement.
    EOEventType
    EOEventType can be linked to one or more EOEvents.
    EOGUI
    Administrates the GUI, what panels are shown and communicates with EOManager, with data the user creates, reads, updates and deletes.
    EOGUIArrangementTable
    The EOGUIArrangementTable is custom made to shows the different EOArrangement, it is used in the EOPanelStartMenu.
    EOGUIBreadcrumb
    Is the visuable breadcrumb class, this is used on all Panels in the program to show the user where they are currently located, and giving them an option to jump to another location in the path.
    EOGUIMultiSelect
    Shows one or more lines of options.
    EOManager
    The EOManager class is the class that talks with the GUI (EOGUI) and the Database (EODatabaseInterface).
    EOPanel
    Our main class for all EOPanel's
    EOPanelADMEventType
    Panel that gives the user the options to Create, Delete, Update EOEventType's.
    EOPanelADMFacilitator
    Administrates the Facilitators, Create, Delete and UPDATE.
    EOPanelCreateArrangement
    Used for when a user needs to create an arrangement
    EOPanelCreateEvent
    The user uses the panel, when they need to create an event.
    EOPanelDeleteArrangement
    Gives the user a visible alert, that the arrangement is about to be deleted.
    EOPanelError
    Shows the default error screen i the program.
    EOPanelExport
    The default export panel, the user uses to export data.
    EOPanelImport
    Shows the user what will happen when data is imported, and gives them the option to import a datafile.
    EOPanelOpenArrangement
    The user can open an arrangement, and read the specific properties from the arrangement through this panel
    EOPanelOpenEvent
    A user can open 1 event and look at its properties through this panel.
    EOPanelOpenEventType
    An user can open one EventType and look at its properties through this panel.
    EOPanelOpenFacilitator
    Opens a facilitator and shows properties for the object through this panel.
    EOPanelStartMenu
    The start menu shows all arrangements, and provides the user options to CRUD arrangements the classes they contains.
    EOPanelUpdateArrangement
    Gives the option for updating an arrangement
    EOPanelUpdateEvent
    Gives the user the option to update and event.
    ExternalContactInfo
    Contains contact information for an external contact.
    FacilitatorContactInfo
    Contains facilitator contact info
    Link
    Contains information for a database link.
    Run
    The run class, is the start class of the program, where we start the EOManager.
    RunDB  
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    EODisplayType
    The EODisplayType is used by the EOGUI to select which Panel to show to the user.
    EOOperation
    All operations in the Event Organizer program is tied to an EOOperation, the EOOperation ENUM tells the program what it must do and it contains the data it must do it with.
